parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Transmission Slipping and Failure to Downshift
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission slipping and failure to downshift can cause loss of power, hesitation, and unexpected acceleration, which can lead to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The transmission slips from one gear to another
especially when cold
the transmission fails to downshift when accelerator is depressed
the transmission does not shift even when shifted manually
the transmission shifts too early
the transmission does not shift at all when gas is applied.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The inability to reset the Engine Control Module (ECM) can cause issues with the vehicle's performance, fuel efficiency, and emission control, leading to decreased vehicle reliability and potential safety hazards.
symptoms: The vehicle's computer system is unable to be reset
the vehicle's performance is affected
the vehicle's fuel efficiency is decreased
the vehicle's emission control system is malfunctioning
the vehicle's dashboard warning lights are illuminated.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Loose Clamps around Gas Tank Causing Gas Fumes
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The loose clamps around the gas tank can cause gas fumes to enter the passenger compartment, which can lead to health risks, discomfort, and potentially even fires or explosions.
symptoms: Strong gas odors or fumes inside the vehicle
headaches
dizziness
or nausea due to gas fume exposure
visible signs of gas leakage around the gas tank area.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The misalignment of the rear suspension can cause uneven tire wear, leading to reduced traction and increased risk of tire failure, which can result in loss of vehicle control and accidents.
symptoms: Uneven tire wear
particularly on the rear tires
pulling or drifting to one side while driving
vibrations or shaking while driving
uneven ride height
loose or worn-out suspension components.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt buckle can cause the occupant to become trapped in the vehicle, increasing the risk of injury or death in the event of an accident or emergency situation.
symptoms: The seat belt buckle will not release
the seat belt is stuck
the occupant is unable to exit the vehicle
the seat belt is difficult to unlatch.
